sql:
SELECT reason, COUNT(*) AS total_churned_customers
FROM churn_rates
GROUP BY reason;

external_knowledge:
- Churn refers to the act of customers stopping their subscription to a service; 
- High-risk customers are those who have not made any payments recently; 
- Medium-risk customers are those who made at least one payment recently; 
- Recent payments are those made within the last 30 days; 
- Risk level assessment helps businesses identify which customers are more likely to cancel their subscription.
